Appendix 20
Such stories are no jokes, although they make this impression when they cross our way in Eurasian folklore. &ldquo;Air&rdquo; is a strictly astronomical and, therefore, also a &ldquo;religious&rdquo; term. Thus, we hear from Rabbi Eleazar b. Pedath (ca. A.D. 270): &ldquo;Als def Pharaoh aus Agypten auszog, die Israeliten zu verfolgen, erhoben sie ihre Augen gen Himmel und sahen den Engelsfürsten Ägyptens in der Luft fliegen.&rdquo;
